  "prompt": "Last year my Thanksgiving turkey was dry, what is the best way to roast a Thanksgiving turkey?",
  "response": "To roast a moist and delicious Thanksgiving turkey, here are some key tips:\n\n1. Brining\n- Brine the turkey overnight in salt water solution\n- This helps keep the meat moist and adds flavor\n- Can use wet or dry brine methods\n\n2. Preparation\n- Pat the turkey dry before roasting\n- Rub butter or oil under the skin and on the outside\n- Season generously with salt, pepper, and herbs\n\n3. Roasting techniques\n- Start with high heat (425\u00b0F) for 30 minutes to crisp the skin\n- Lower temperature to 325\u00b0F for remainder of cooking\n- Use a meat thermometer to ensure proper internal temperature (165\u00b0F)\n- Cover with foil if browning too quickly\n\n4. Additional tips\n- Let turkey rest 20-30 minutes after cooking\n- Use a roasting rack to allow air circulation\n- Baste occasionally with pan juices\n- Consider stuffing herb butter under the skin\n- Don't overcook - use a meat thermometer\n\n5. Optional methods\n- Spatchcocking (removing backbone for more even cooking)\n- Using a roasting bag\n- Slow roasting at a lower temperature\n\nThese methods will help ensure a juicy, flavorful turkey.",
